	<div class="header">
		<span class="comment-link"><a href="#comment-57427" title="comment permalink">#26</a></span>
		<span class="fn">ThomasT</span>
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c1465d7d5de6d9676508d8ed3ff1ecf8?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' />		
		<div>Thailand</div>
		April 8, 2013		<span class="report"></span>
			</div>
	<div class="content">
		<p>The age of the Universe  just a few billion years?  Our scientists still have much to learn. There are 10 to the power of 49 Universes in the &#8216;Absolutum&#8217;.  We are one of them. Every Universe has an awake  period 311 trillion year. We are in the 47th trillion year of the cycle in this Universe.</p>
<p>Open <a href="http://www.theyfly.com" rel="nofollow">http://www.theyfly.com</a> and see where this info comes from, and read The Pleiadian Mission by Randolph Winters for the fine points. </p>
<p>Before you scream fraud, consider that the Swiss et conactee Meier published info from et re our solar system,often years ahead of nasa&#8217;s discoveries.</p>
<p>If you want to believe we are alone, themost high tech in the Universe, and came from chimp, that is none of my business.</p>
	</div>
</div><!--/comment-->	</div>
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

<li class="li-comment" id="li-comment-57436">
	<div class="div-comment" id="div-comment-57436">
<div id="comment-57436" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 reply">
	<div class="header">
		<span class="comment-link"><a href="#comment-57436" title="comment permalink">#27</a></span>
		<span class="fn">MG</span>
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6062daea563dc4ce4ff62fe1fa6f4aa8?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' />		
		<div>USA</div>
		April 8, 2013		<span class="report"></span>
			</div>
	<div class="content">
		<p>Semmel &#8211;<br />
How disingenuous for such comments to originate from a nation only 75 years removed from the definitive example of why a strong military is needed to protect our civilization. The fact is that human nature has been proven over and over again to be corrupt, evil and ethnocentric. Without a defense which is at least as powerful as the self-appointed &#8220;master race&#8221;, all science and knowledge will be subverted, and academic freedom will be lost. So remember that while one hand holds the sword, the other holds the shield, and the outcome is the result of both.</p>
	</div>
</div><!--/comment-->	</div>
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

