<li class="li-comment" id="li-comment-57463">
	<div class="div-comment" id="div-comment-57463">
<div id="comment-57463" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 reply">
	<div class="header">
		<span class="comment-link"><a href="#comment-57463" title="comment permalink">#29</a></span>
		<span class="fn">Robert Newton</span>
		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/368f19815e1a703fa23bd94302b9bab4?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' />		
		<div></div>
		April 9, 2013		<span class="report"></span>
			</div>
	<div class="content">
		<p>@ Douglas Watts #13:<br />
Sorry Douglas, but Ethan is correct.  Only the overblown human ego can think otherwise. Our biggest threat is to ourselves &#8211; not to planet Earth, which will certainly survive anything we can throw at it. What&#8217;s in doubt is whether we can survive the conditions we bring about.  The Earth will spin on regardless.  We need the Earth to survive. It DOESN&#8217;T need us.</p>
	</div>
</div><!--/comment-->	</div>
